        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 5:02PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Fayetteville, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fayetteville, Raeford, Fort Bragg, Antioch, Hope Mills, Silver City,
Rockfish, and Bonnie Doone.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
